Splinters (ie: Double-Jump-Shifts like 1@S-4@D) sit happily with Precision, but in practice this system doesn't normally use them. 

They are used to show game-going hands potentially interested in a slam. They agree Opener's Major as trumps and show a strong hand (usually 16+) and a singleton/void in the suit bid. 

